'''WISE J224607.57−052635.0'''(或簡寫為'''W2246−0526''')<ref name="NASA-20181115" />是一個[[亮紅外星系#特亮紅外星系|特亮紅外星系]]， 2015年，它被宣告為[[宇宙|宇宙]]中已知最亮的[[星系|星系]]<ref name="NASA-20181115">{{cite web |last1=Cofield |first1=Calla |last2=Blue |first2=Charles |title=The Most Luminous Galaxy Is Eating Its Neighbors |url=https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=7282 |date=15 November 2018 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=15 November 2018 |archive-date=2019-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213020753/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=7282 }}</ref><ref name="SCI-20181115">{{cite journal |author=Diaz-Santos, T.|display-authors=etal |title=The multiple merger assembly of a hyperluminous obscured quasar at redshift 4.6 |date=15 November 2018 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=362 |issue=6416 |pages=1034–1036 |doi=10.1126/science.aap7605 |pmid=30442765 |arxiv=1811.05992 |bibcode=2018Sci...362.1034D |s2cid=53567900 }}</ref><ref name="AJ-20181114">{{cite journal |author=Tsai, Chao-Wei|display-authors=etal |title=Super-Eddington Accretion in the WISE-selected Extremely Luminous Infrared Galaxy W2246−0526 |date=14 November 2018 |journal=[[The_Astrophysical_Journal|The Astrophysical Journal]] |volume=868 |pages=15 |number=1 |doi=10.3847/1538-4357/aae698 |arxiv=1810.02933 |bibcode=2018ApJ...868...15T |s2cid=119477702 }}</ref>。它的[[太陽光度|光度]]是[[太陽|太陽]]的350兆倍<ref name="NASA-20181115" />(太陽（349×10<sup>12</sup>{{solar luminosity}}<ref name="ARX-20150408"/>)，與附近較小星系的合併可能是其特別亮的原因之一<ref name="NASA-20181115" /><ref name="SCI-20181115" /><ref name="AJ-20181114" />。光度是由一個質量為太陽100億倍的類星體產生的。在[[類星體|類星體]]中環繞[[超大質量黑洞|超大質量黑洞]]的[[吸積盤|吸積盤]] 輻射出的可見光和超紫外線，被星系的[[宇宙塵埃|塵埃]]吸收，然後以[[紅外線|紅外線]]匯出。儘管WISE J224607.57–052635.0是兩者之中較小的一個星系，但它是出的能量是[[銀河系|銀河系]]的10,000倍。WISE J224607.57–052635.0這個星系是由[[廣域紅外線巡天探測衛星|廣域紅外線巡天探測衛星]]發現的，它與地球的距離是125億[[光年|光年]]<ref name="ARX-20150408">{{cite journal |last1=Tsai |first1=Chao-Wei |display-authors=etal|title=The Most Luminous Galaxies Discovered by WISE|journal=The Astrophysical Journal|date=22 May 2015|volume=805|issue=2|pages=90|doi=10.1088/0004-637X/805/2/90|arxiv = 1410.1751 |bibcode = 2015ApJ...805...90T |s2cid=39280020 }}</ref><ref name="PO-20150521">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=WISE spacecraft discovers most luminous galaxy in universe |url=http://phys.org/news/2015-05-wise-spacecraft-luminous-galaxy-universe.html |date=21 May 2015 |website=PhysOrg |access-date=22 May 2015 |archive-date=2015-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522115033/http://phys.org/news/2015-05-wise-spacecraft-luminous-galaxy-universe.html }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20150521">{{cite web |title=PIA19339: Dusty 'Sunrise' at Core of Galaxy (Artist's Concept) |url=http://photojournal.jpl.nasa.gov/catalog/PIA19339 |date=21 May 2015 |publisher=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=21 May 2015 |archive-date=2019-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506000856/https://photojournal.jpl.nasa.gov/catalog/PIA19339 }}</ref><ref name="NASA-20150521a">{{cite web |last1=Chou |first1=Felicia |last2=Clavin |first2=Whitney |title=NASA's WISE Spacecraft Discovers Most Luminous Galaxy in Universe |url=http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasas-wise-spacecraft-discovers-most-luminous-galaxy-in-universe |date=21 May 2015 |access-date=25 May 2015 |archive-date=2019-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617085014/https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasas-wise-spacecraft-discovers-most-luminous-galaxy-in-universe/ }}</ref><ref name="NG-20150526">{{cite web |last1=Lemonick |first1=Michael D. |title=Brightest Galaxy Yet Shines With Light of 300 Trillion Suns |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/05/150526-astronomy-brightest-galaxy-quasar-universe |date=26 May 2015 |work=[[National_Geographic_News|National Geographic News]] |access-date=27 May 2015 |archive-date=2019-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506000918/https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/05/150526-astronomy-brightest-galaxy-quasar-universe/ }}</ref>。
